         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 15/4/75 ¶  ¶ At last, rev. and venerable friend, I have succeeded after almost endless writings to obtain from one of the localities of the  ¶ Horse-hair fungus ¶  fruiting specimens throu...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">75.04.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Miles Berkeley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Natural History Museum, London, Botany Library, Berkeley correspondence, vol. 9.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/4/75</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At last, rev. and venerable friend, I have succeeded after almost endless writings to obtain from one of the localities of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Horse-hair fungus</hi>
               </seg> fruiting specimens through the persevering circumspectness of Mrs Mary Hogdkinson, residing on the Richmond River in New South Wales. It seems to be a true <name key="Agaricus">Agaricus</name> or belongs perhaps to one of the genera by modern writers separated. This fungus is now known from East Gipps-land,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> where it grows on the Branches of <name key="Aster%20argophyllus">Aster argophyllus</name> (Taylor), near Sydney (Ramsay), Richmond River (Mrs Hodgkinson), Rockingham's Bay<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
               </note> (Lieut. Armit). I have not dissected it, as there are only the few pilei, all now transmitted, which I did not like to break up, they being so small. If therefore this species should be new and not belong to <name key="Agaricus">Agaricus</name> in the sense of recent writers, then — pray — do not mention the name, under which I would propose to render it known with our united authority.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The name M proposed to Berkeley has not been found. The species concerned may be the one named by M as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Marasmius equi-crinis</seg> in B80.02.02, p. 90, citing specimens from Hodgkinson (Richmond River) and Taylor (East Gippsland). </p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall be glad to have your opinion on this remarkable plant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With deep regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>always your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Agaricus">Agaricus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Aster%20argophyllus">Aster argophyllus</name>
            </p>
